The rand continued to drop to record lows  against the dollar, opening here Monday at 3.6525/40 to the greenback from  Friday's close of 3.6440/55.
Dealers said the local unit was suffering from continued dollar strength  and would likely remain weak against the U.S. currency.
The fianncial rand for non-resident investors opened at 4.92/94 to the  dollar, down from its previous close of 4.88/90.
Gold opened at 380.00/50 dollars an ounce, down slightly from Friday's New  York close of 380.50/381.00.
Other currencies were:
